description: Creates a new queue for the specified Amazon Connect instance.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instance ID in the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the instance.

parameters.name: OutboundCallerConfig
parameters.description: The outbound caller ID name, number, and outbound whisper flow. OutboundCallerIdName (string) --- The caller ID name. OutboundCallerIdNumberId (string) --- The caller ID number. OutboundFlowId (string) --- The outbound whisper flow to be used during an outbound call.

nested_params.name: OutboundFlowId
nested_params.description: The outbound whisper flow to be used during an outbound call.

parameters.name: OutboundEmailConfig
parameters.description: The outbound email address ID for a specified queue. OutboundEmailAddressId (string) --- The identifier of the email address.

nested_params.name: OutboundEmailAddressId
nested_params.description: The identifier of the email address.

parameters.name: HoursOfOperationId
parameters.description: The identifier for the hours of operation.

parameters.name: QuickConnectIds
parameters.description: The quick connects available to agents who are working the queue. (string) ---

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: The tags used to organize, track, or control access for this resource. For example, { 'Tags': {'key1':'value1', 'key2':'value2'} }. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_items.name: QueueArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the queue.
